---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="About ouroboros and the person behind it."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<header class="page-header">
				<h1 class="page-title">About</h1>
			</header>
			<div class="prose">
				<p>
					ouroboros is a writing project about software, systems, and the ideas that connect them.
					It's where I think through things that seem obvious until you look closely.
				</p>
				<p>
					The name is deliberate. An ouroboros is a snake eating its own tail — a symbol of
					cycles, self-reference, and recursive regeneration. Most interesting problems in software
					have this shape: understanding something by building it, building it to understand it.
				</p>
				<p>
					I'm Eyal. I write about the things I find worth thinking twice about. I also run
					<a href="https://argo-navis.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">argo-navis.net</a>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		max-width: 680px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: var(--space-16) var(--space-6) 0;
	}

	.page-header {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
	}

	.page-title {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		font-size: var(--text-4xl);
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		color: var(--text-primary);
		margin: 0;
	}

	@media (max-width: 480px) {
		main {
			padding: var(--space-10) var(--space-4) 0;
		}
	}
</style>
